searchExResultDTO Data Type

A single result from an elastic search

Namespace
(Default)
Properties
name data type type namespace min/max occurs description
inc_id int element 0/1 The id of the incident to which the search result belongs. If the search result is an incident, then inc_id is identical to obj_id.
inc_name string element 0/1 The name of the incident to which the search result belongs. If the search result is an incident, then inc_name is identical to obj_name.
inc_owner_id objectHandle element 0/1 The name of the owner of the incident to which the search result belongs. If the search result is an incident, then inc_owner is identical to obj_owner.
match_field_name string element 0/1 The name of the search field where a match was found.
match_field_value string element 0/1 The value of the search field where a match was found, including an indication of what term(s) matched the full text search.
obj_create_date dateTime element 0/1 The creation date of the search result. This can be null for results which do not have a creation date stored.
obj_creator_id objectHandle element 0/1 The name of the creator of the search result. Datatables do not support a creator, so search results of that type would be null.
obj_id int element 0/1 The unique identifier of the search result
obj_name string element 0/1 The name of the search result object. In the case of a data table row, this name represents the programmatic name of the data table. Can be null for objects with no names (e.g. notes)
obj_owner_id objectHandle element 0/1 The name of the owner of the search result. Search results of types milestone, artifact, attachment and datatable do not support the notion of 'owner' so the value would be null. In the case of a comment (type = note), obj_owner_id would represent a user who has subsequently modified the comment. If it hasn't been modified, this value would be null.
obj_state string element 0/1 The state of the search result. This is only applicable for incidents and tasks.
org_id int element 0/1 The unique identifier of the Organization that this search result belongs to.
result anyType element 0/1 The actual object returned by the search
score float element 1/1 A score value for the search hit
task_id int element 0/1 The id of the task to which the search result belongs. This is only populated for task, task attachment, and task notes. In the case of task, task_id is identical to obj_id. If the search result belongs to an incident only (i.e. incident, incident note, incident attachment, artifact or datatable) then this result is null.
task_name string element 0/1 The name of the task to which the search result belongs. This is only populated for task, task attachment, and task notes. In the case of task, task_name is identical to obj_name. If the search result belongs to an incident only (i.e. incident, incident note, incident attachment, artifact or datatable) then this result is null.
type_id typeId element 0/1 The type id of the result . Must be one of the following: 
 incident
 task
 note
 milestone
 artifact
 attachment
 datatable
For more information about type ids, refer to this
